<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2><span style="font-size:16pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Data as public good</span></span></h2>
<p><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">With data being the new oil in the 4th Industrial Revolution the Economic Survey has mooted it being treated as a public good.</span></span></p>
<p><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Cycle of data</span></span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h4><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Benefits/Needs:</span></span></h4>
<ol>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Economic:</span></span>
<ol>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">data can be monetized and used to raise finances.e.g: Min of Housing selling Indian Urban Data Exchange to private companies</span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">it will help generate jobs in data analysis, processing and mining</span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Agricultural market developed. E-NAM</span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">promote innovation e.g. Open bankin g</span></span></li></ol></li>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Administrative:</span></span>
<ol>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">&nbsp;helps in better targeting of scheme, reduce exclusion errors.e.g: DBT in MGNREGS</span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">end to end governance</span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">evidence based policy making</span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Participation of NGOs etc up eg. Data analysis for effectiveness of public policy</span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha">&nbsp;</li></ol></li>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Security:</span></span>
<ol>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">can reduce crime.e.g: CCTNS and DNA Technology Bill 2019</span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Defence: holistic answer to security challenges.e.g: NATGRID.</span></span></li></ol></li>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Environmental: it will help track progress in efforts.e.g: m-Stripes Tiger Survey.</span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Disaster Management: Better weather forecasting and timely action #eg : INCOIS IFC (info fusion centre)&nbsp;</span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Political: correlation between national identity and data can be seen in Aadhar Card and NRC exercise</span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Science n Tech: data is key input for new frontier tech-AI and Machine learning.</span></span></li></ol>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h4><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Challenges</span></span></h4>
<ul>
<li style="list-style-type:disc"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Absence of data protection law</span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:disc"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">data as a resource must not be monopolized by one company(especially foreign)</span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:disc"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">lack of processing infrastructure</span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:disc"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Issue of data localisation: most generation is through foreign co-Google, Facebook,Uber.</span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:disc"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">misrepresentation of data in form of deepfakes and fake news.</span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:disc"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">misuse of data in politics needs to be checked by ECI</span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:disc"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Issues surrounding privacy (Need to follow BN Shrikrishna Commission)</span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:disc"><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">ethical issues: should all data be protected or transparent</span></span></li></ul>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><span style="font-size:13pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Data must be democratised as it is of the people,by the people and for the people.</span></span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>